ain-eye-16535/" class="mask-img"><img width="849" height="609" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20849%20609'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-zeen-390-390 size-zeen-390-390 wp-post-image" alt="This shows brain scans from the study" data-lazy-src="https://neurosciencenews.com/files/2020/06/moral-reflection-brain-eye-neuroscneews-849x609.jpg" /><noscript><img width="849" height="609" src="https://neurosciencenews.com/files/2020/06/moral-reflection-brain-eye-neuroscneews-849x609.jpg" class="attachment-zeen-390-390 size-zeen-390-390 wp-post-image" alt="This shows brain scans from the study" /></noscript></a></div><div class="meta"><div class="byline byline-2 byline-cats-design-4"><div class="byline-part cats"><a href="https://neurosciencenews.com/neuroscience-topics/featured/" style="color:#0d58db" class="cat">Featured</a><a href="https://neurosciencenews.com/neuroscience-topics/neuroscience/" style="color:#0d58db" class="cat">Neuroscience</a><a href="https://neurosciencenews.com/neuroscience-topics/open-neuroscience-articles/" style="color:#81d742" class="cat">Open Neuroscience Articles</a><a href="https://neurosciencenews.com/neuroscience-topics/psychology/" style="color:#f4d122" class="cat">Psychology</a></div><span class="byline-part separator separator-date">&middot;</span><span class="byline-part date"><time class="entry-date published dateCreated flipboard-date" datetime="2020-06-13T12:12:57-07:00">June 13, 2020</time></span></div><div class="title-wrap"><h3 class="title"><a href="https://neurosciencenews.com/moral-reflection-brain-eye-16535/">Moral reflection can be seen in brain activity and eye movements</a></h3></div><div class="excerpt body-color">Using scenes from movies, researchers discover how different brain areas can be used flexibly and as needed. The study sheds light on how the brain transitions between moral thinking and empathy. <span class="read-more-wrap font-3"><a class="read-more" href="https: